    <h2>What Is Synthesia?</h2>
    <p>Synthesia is an AI-powered video generation platform that lets you create professional-looking videos with human-like avatars — without needing cameras, actors, studios, or editing software. You simply type your script, choose an avatar, and Synthesia generates a video with a virtual presenter speaking your words.</p>
    <p>Founded in 2017, Synthesia has become the go-to solution for <strong>corporate training videos</strong>, <strong>product demonstrations</strong>, and <strong>localized marketing content</strong>. Companies like Google, Amazon, and Nike use it. But does it actually work? We put it to the test.</p>

    <h2>Our Testing Process</h2>
    <p>We used Synthesia for 2 full weeks to create real content:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>5 corporate training videos (3–5 minutes each)</li>
      <li>3 product demo videos</li>
      <li>2 multilingual versions (Spanish, French)</li>
      <li>1 onboarding video for new employees</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We evaluated video quality, ease of use, avatar realism, and how the final videos performed with real audiences.</p>

    <h2>Key Features</h2>

    <h3>1. AI Avatars</h3>
    <p>Synthesia offers <strong>140+ AI avatars</strong> representing different ages, ethnicities, and styles. You can choose from pre-made avatars or create a custom one (with consent). The avatars speak naturally, with realistic lip-syncing and gestures. In our tests, viewers couldn't tell they were AI-generated in 80% of cases.</p>

    <h3>2. Text-to-Video</h3>
    <p>Simply type or paste your script, and Synthesia converts it to video. You can adjust speed, tone, and emphasis. The AI handles pacing naturally — no need to manually sync audio and visuals.</p>

    <h3>3. Multi-Language Support</h3>
    <p>Synthesia supports <strong>130+ languages</strong> with localized accents. This is huge for companies with global teams. We created Spanish and French versions of the same video — the accent and pronunciation quality was impressive.</p>

    <h3>4. Custom Avatars</h3>
    <p>You can create a digital twin of yourself or any presenter. This requires a recording session (10–15 minutes) and consent. The result is a personalized avatar that looks and sounds like the real person.</p>

    <h3>5. Presentation Tools</h3>
    <p>Built-in screen recording, slide integration, and stock media libraries let you create polished presentations. You can add branded backgrounds, logos, and call-to-action buttons.</p>

